title: Kis Uykusu
overview: A hotel owner and landlord in a remote Turkish village deals with conflicts within his family and a tenant behind on his rent.

title: Midnight Cowboy
overview: A naive hustler travels from Texas to New York City to seek personal fortune, finding a new friend in the process.

title: Soorarai Pottru
overview: Nedumaaran Rajangam "Maara" sets out to make the common man fly and in the process takes on the world's most capital intensive industry and several enemies who stand in his way.

title: Gran Torino
overview: Disgruntled Korean War veteran Walt Kowalski sets out to reform his neighbor, Thao Lor, a Hmong teenager who tried to steal Kowalski's prized possession: a 1972 Gran Torino.

title: Jodaeiye Nader az Simin
overview: A married couple are faced with a difficult decision - to improve the life of their child by moving to another country or to stay in Iran and look after a deteriorating parent who has Alzheimer's disease.

title: Django Unchained
overview: With the help of a German bounty hunter, a freed slave sets out to rescue his wife from a brutal Mississippi plantation owner.

title: Boogie Nights
overview: Back when sex was safe, pleasure was a business and business was booming, an idealistic porn producer aspires to elevate his craft to an art when he discovers a hot young talent.

title: Philadelphia
overview: When a man with HIV is fired by his law firm because of his condition, he hires a homophobic small time lawyer as the only willing advocate for a wrongful dismissal suit.

title: Donnie Darko
overview: After narrowly escaping a bizarre accident, a troubled teenager is plagued by visions of a man in a large rabbit suit who manipulates him to commit a series of crimes.

title: Forrest Gump
overview: The presidencies of Kennedy and Johnson, the events of Vietnam, Watergate and other historical events unfold through the perspective of an Alabama man with an IQ of 75, whose only desire is to be reunited with his childhood sweetheart.

title: Auf der anderen Seite
overview: A Turkish man travels to Istanbul to find the daughter of his father's former girlfriend.

title: Synecdoche, New York
overview: A theatre director struggles with his work, and the women in his life, as he creates a life-size replica of New York City inside a warehouse as part of his new play.

title: The Florida Project
overview: Set over one summer, the film follows precocious six-year-old Moonee as she courts mischief and adventure with her ragtag playmates and bonds with her rebellious but caring mother, all while living in the shadows of Walt Disney World.

title: Billy Elliot
overview: A talented young boy becomes torn between his unexpected love of dance and the disintegration of his family.

title: Black Swan
overview: A committed dancer struggles to maintain her sanity after winning the lead role in a production of Tchaikovsky's "Swan Lake".

title: Citizen Kane
overview: Following the death of publishing tycoon Charles Foster Kane, reporters scramble to uncover the meaning of his final utterance; 'Rosebud'.

title: American Beauty
overview: A sexually frustrated suburban father has a mid-life crisis after becoming infatuated with his daughter's best friend.

title: Le passé
overview: An Iranian man deserts his French wife and her two children to return to his homeland. Meanwhile, his wife starts up a new relationship, a reality her husband confronts upon his wife's request for a divorce.

title: American History X
overview: A former neo-nazi skinhead tries to prevent his younger brother from going down the same wrong path that he did.

title: Nuovo Cinema Paradiso
overview: A filmmaker recalls his childhood when falling in love with the pictures at the cinema of his home village and forms a deep friendship with the cinema's projectionist.
